{"id": "EUVD-2025-201872", "enisaUuid": "a1408277-6b33-39a6-99c0-27ed6abb8bdf", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nbnxt_en: Shutdown FW DMA in bnxt_shutdown()\n\nThe netif_close() call in bnxt_shutdown() only stops packet DMA.  There\nmay be FW DMA for trace logging (recently added) that will continue.  If\nwe kexec to a new kernel, the DMA will corrupt memory in the new kernel.\n\nAdd bnxt_hwrm_func_drv_unrgtr() to unregister the driver from the FW.\nThis will stop the FW DMA.  In case the call fails, call pcie_flr() to\nreset the function and stop the DMA.", "datePublished": "2025-12-09T18:30:35", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-09T18:30:35", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1a8a15c3f71d1199d510ccba4bc201cbd2204048", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/bc7208ca805ae6062f353a4753467d913d963bc6", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-40330"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-40330"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0943a723-3051-33ca-bb71-c696ecb35c43", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.13"}, {"id": "13bd1922-7c77-3228-aa74-d2429779a2f3", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.18"}, {"id": "388dffe1-3b2b-3555-9156-024c10f77633", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "24d694aec139e9e0a31c60993db79bd8ad575afe <1a8a15c3f71d1199d510ccba4bc201cbd2204048"}, {"id": "6a83f0e1-6e4c-37af-a502-fac992afa935", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "24d694aec139e9e0a31c60993db79bd8ad575afe <bc7208ca805ae6062f353a4753467d913d963bc6"}, {"id": "e1fb643b-5f20-3068-8572-91297893989b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.17.8"}, {"id": "ee436efc-7e4e-30dd-a81f-c5f642bf6619", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "05f9a93b-6484-3159-9201-2ed51956806f", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}